original: Jernberg, Eric T., verkstadsingenjör, Skövde, f. 18/7/92 i Södertälje av dir. P. Th. J. o. Alma Hermansson. G. 29’ m. Anna Hansson. — Örebro tekn. gymn. 11. Prakt. o. stud. i mek. v. aftonsk. i USA 20, 21-32. Anst. v. Centrifug A-B i Södertäaje 11-18, v. A-B Haldex i Halmstad 34-38, verkstadschef h. A-B Volvo i Skövde fr. 39. Ordf. i Tekn. fören. i Skövde 43-46, ordf. i Skövde högerfören. Medl. av Frimurarorden fr. 41.
translated: Jernberg, Eric T., mechanical engineer, Skövde, born on July 18, 1892 in Södertälje to director P. Th. J. and Alma Hermansson. Married in 1929 to Anna Hansson. Completed Örebro technical gymnasium in 1911. Practical and studied mechanical engineering at evening school in the USA from 1920 to 1921-1932. Employed at Centrifug A-B in Södertäaje from 1911 to 1918, at A-B Haldex in Halmstad from 1934 to 1938, and as works manager at A-B Volvo in Skövde starting from 1939. Chairman of the Technical Association in Skövde from 1943 to 1946, chairman of the Skövde right-wing association. Member of the Freemasonry Order from 1941.
